Sugar Prices May Drop on Brazil Production Outlook, Survey Says

-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m   a n d   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-06-09T23:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/sugar-prices-may-drop-on-brazil-production-outlook-survey-says.html
Sugar may fall next week on bets an
industry group will report higher output in  Brazil .  Seven of 10 traders, analysts and brokers surveyed by
Bloomberg News said raw sugar traded in New York may decline.
Two said it may gain. One was neutral. Before today, futures for
October delivery gained 1.6 percent this week to 23.99 cents a
pound on ICE Futures U.S.  Six of 10 respondents said refined sugar on  London ’s NYSE
Liffe will drop. Two said it may rise, and two forecast little
change. Futures were up 2.7 percent this week through yesterday.  Refined sugar’s premium over raw sweetener may be little
changed next week, four respondents said. Three said it may
narrow, and three said it will widen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Justin Doom in  New York  at 
